SIMPLE: tithingman
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tithingman
<hw>Tith"ing*man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Tithingmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(O. Eng.
Law)</fld> <def>The chief man of a tithing; a headborough; one elected
to preside over the tithing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A peace officer; an under
constable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A parish officer elected annually to preserve good
order in the church during divine service, to make complaint of any
disorderly conduct, and to enforce the observance of the Sabbath.</def>
<mark>[Local, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tithly</ent>⟦br⟧
